He’s one of only four players to average at least 20 points, five rebounds and five assists last year, but knee problems during the playoffs have led to him fielding questions about his perceived decline. Wade is going into his 11th Miami season, and it would seem like there’s a strong chance he could be in the Eastern Conference finals for the sixth time. With three rings already, he’s playing for legacy now.
